Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.68,0:01:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Quatre.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.25,0:01:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.91,0:01:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell the others for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.38,0:01:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell them to stay away.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.82,0:01:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.62,0:01:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll kill them.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.99,0:01:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I told you to stay away!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.70,0:01:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that all you've got\Nto say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.04,0:01:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,If everything has gone mad...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.64,0:01:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,...then I'll just fight,\Nbelieving in myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.44,0:02:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Quatre, I'm gonna kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.52,0:03:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The shield won't hold\Nmuch longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.83,0:03:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Heero...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.83,0:03:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are we fighting each other?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.87,0:03:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The colonies have\Nteamed up with OZ.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.87,0:03:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The colonies are my enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.87,0:03:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}They're your enemies{\i0}\N{\i1}now too, Trowa and Heero.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.38,0:03:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,People in space have\Nlost all reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.78,0:03:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I'm gonna\Ndestroy everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.65,0:03:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That's natural isn't it, Heero?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.10,0:04:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You'll die, Heero.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.30,0:04:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,But I don't want to defeat\Nmy allies.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.27,0:04:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Please Heero, get away\Nfrom here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.21,0:04:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you listening to me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.84,0:04:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Quatre.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.45,0:04:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.11,0:04:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's a colony that needs\Nto be defended.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.94,0:04:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Heero.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.91,0:04:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I can't stand that colony{\i0}\N{\i1}any longer.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.51,0:04:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We've lost communication with\NTrowa Barton's Vayeate...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.68,0:04:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,...and the Leo unit that's\Nfighting the Gundam!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.99,0:04:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole unit, including the\NMercurius, may be wiped out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.06,0:04:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And the colony?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.09,0:04:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.09,0:05:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the colony still there?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.99,0:05:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, so far it's been spared\Nany significant damage.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.26,0:05:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That means the battle\Nis still going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.60,0:05:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Righteous Gundam pilots would\Nfight to protect the colonies.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.90,0:05:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Hopefully they'll be able to\Nstop this new Gundam.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.41,0:05:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Images from the mother\Nship of Leo's unit.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.61,0:05:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.35,0:05:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Now send these to the Gundam\Nengineers at the Lunar Base.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.42,0:05:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We should be able to find out\Nsomething from them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.79,0:05:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But Colonel.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.09,0:05:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't communicate with\Nthe Lunar Base right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.82,0:05:33.45,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.30,0:05:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief Engineer Tubarov!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.53,0:05:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We've just received orders\Nfrom Fortress Barge...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.97,0:05:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,...to restore communication.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.30,0:05:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Never mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.80,0:05:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We must follow the orders\Nfrom Duke Dermail...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.67,0:05:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,...to speed up mobile doll\Nproduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.24,0:05:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,There appears to be some\Nunrest within Romefeller.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.78,0:05:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,People cannot be trusted.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.95,0:05:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We're entering an age\Nwhere mobile dolls...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.35,0:06:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,...will be our new warriors.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.42,0:06:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You old guys seem calm\Nconsidering it won't be long...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.62,0:06:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,...before the air is gone\Nand we start passing out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.06,0:06:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We haven't even got our\Nrevenge against OZ yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.13,0:06:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What a lousy way to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.30,0:06:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I sure wish I could've seen\Nthat new Gundam, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.17,0:06:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,We didn't finish upgrading\Nthe Deathscythe and Shenlong.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.04,0:06:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Such a shame.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.75,0:06:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,My words, exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.43,0:06:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I never would've guessed\NI'd be dying like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.63,0:06:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Wu Fei.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.67,0:06:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,My Deathscythe is pretty\Ncool, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.67,0:06:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd demolish OZ with this\Nin no time!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.04,0:06:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.71,0:07:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you already dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.25,0:07:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, Wu Fei.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.72,0:07:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't go deserting me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.78,0:07:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Stick with me to the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.56,0:07:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,He's totally stopped breathing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.39,0:07:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,He's in a state of\Nsuspended animation.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.49,0:07:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,This guy's unbelievable.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.66,0:07:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,He refuses to give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.67,0:07:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It makes perfect sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.37,0:07:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Who'd wanna die like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.81,0:07:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The Gundams...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.78,0:07:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The Gundams can't afford\Nto lose at this point.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.86,0:07:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'd ask you to get out{\i0}\N{\i1}of your mobile suit.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.06,0:07:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But you wouldn't.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.59,0:07:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'll just have to kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.46,0:07:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Then get it over with.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.40,0:07:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't sit here and gab\Nwith an enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.84,0:07:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Good-bye, Heero.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.45,0:08:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Quatre.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.22,0:08:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you realize what\Na big mistake you're making?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.89,0:08:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Trowa!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.66,0:08:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This battle is unnecessary.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.17,0:08:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Trowa, escape!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.54,0:08:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The Vayeate's gonna explode!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.27,0:08:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Well.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.84,0:08:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the end of the line.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.98,0:08:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Trowa!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.11,0:08:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,No, Heero!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.35,0:08:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Save Trowa!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.40,0:08:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Trowa!!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.37,0:09:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Quatre.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.63,0:09:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't matter how the\Ncolonies and OZ teamed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.84,0:09:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to keep\Nin mind...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.17,0:09:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,...that it marks the end\Nto a war.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.38,0:09:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It also means our missions\Nhave come to an end.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.35,0:09:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's too bad that the colonies{\i0}\N{\i1}we've been fighting for...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.35,0:09:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}...have changed their{\i0}\N{\i1}perspectives.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.79,0:09:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But that's what happens{\i0}\N{\i1}in wars.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.82,0:09:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We've got to accept that.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.49,0:09:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The only question is what{\i0}\N{\i1}happens to the soldiers.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.73,0:09:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What happens within{\i0}\N{\i1}our hearts.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.30,0:09:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,With us Gundam pilots...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.07,0:09:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,...we were trained to be too\Nperfect as soldiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.44,0:09:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,When you put everything\Ninto a battle...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.87,0:09:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,...you start to think you can\Nchange the times by yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.55,0:09:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Quatre, you're not the only{\i0}\N{\i1}one who feels that way.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.52,0:09:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We all do.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.55,0:09:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But the kinder you are, the{\i0}\N{\i1}bigger the toll it takes on you.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.22,0:10:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We have to fight with ourselves,{\i0}\N{\i1}within our hearts.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.93,0:10:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And we have to be strict to{\i0}\N{\i1}come to the right conclusions.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.03,0:10:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Even if it means our battles{\i0}\N{\i1}to date are meaningless.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.80,0:10:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to acknowledge\Nthe facts.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.30,0:10:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The five of us have become\Nredundant soldiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.64,0:10:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So Quatre, let's accept it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.35,0:10:23.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Turn back into the kind\Nguy you once were.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.48,0:10:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I just hope something{\i0}\N{\i1}triggers you to calm down.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.09,0:10:31.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Something triggers you...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.33,0:10:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Trowa!!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.93,0:10:43.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Heero, let me go!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.44,0:10:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Trowa's gonna die!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.24,0:10:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And you killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.71,0:10:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Heero...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.05,0:10:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You've gone crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.15,0:10:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.58,0:11:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Well hurry and kill me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.82,0:11:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Then go and rescue Trowa!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.62,0:11:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Pretty halfhearted way\Nto fight!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.99,0:11:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess Trowa's death was\Njust a waste!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.84,0:11:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Quatre.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.00,0:11:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm...gonna...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.77,0:11:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,...kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.71,0:11:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Heero!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.31,0:11:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Heero!!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.02,0:11:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be too hard\Non Quatre, Heero.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.67,0:11:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,With the financial power of\Nthe Romefeller Foundation...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.40,0:11:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,...a revolution in technological\Nskills in space is possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.51,0:12:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The system for mass-production\Nof mobile dolls is almost ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.94,0:12:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,As the ruling class to be,\Nwe will position mobile dolls...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.65,0:12:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,...in dispute-ridden regions\Nin each country.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.12,0:12:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus gentlemen, we will\Nshow the entire world...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.05,0:12:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,...how powerful we are,\Nand bring order to the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.16,0:12:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it not time for us\Nto recreate an era...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.56,0:12:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,...with tradition and\Nformality...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.76,0:12:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,...so we can govern\Nthe world properly?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.31,0:12:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Treize, OZ is relying on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.48,0:12:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Duke Dermail.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.78,0:12:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't support the Romefeller\NFoundation's current path.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.15,0:12:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.52,0:12:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Tradition is a kind of history.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.55,0:12:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the history of sympathy,\Nbuilt on people's true feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.13,0:12:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I think fighting in wars\Ncan indeed be beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.13,0:12:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd also like to express my\Nregret over the lost souls...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.50,0:13:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,...by appealing to how\Npriceless man's life is.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.17,0:13:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe what mankind needs\Nis not absolute victory...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.64,0:13:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,...but a certain demeanor in\Nfighting, an attitude towards it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.38,0:13:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I fear the era of the soulless\Nweapons called mobile dolls...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.32,0:13:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,...in other words the era\NRomefeller is creating...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.75,0:13:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,...may be an embarrassment\Nto the people of the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.52,0:13:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to think that the ideals\Nof Space Colonies people...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.03,0:13:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,...such as their highly\Npraised pacifism...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.86,0:13:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,...were pitiful complaints born\Nof their ignorance of tradition.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.60,0:13:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Deathscythe.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.37,0:13:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't give up too easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.77,0:13:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll be okay, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.38,0:13:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,About to commence second test.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.32,0:13:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.86,0:13:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,NO!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.16,0:14:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.63,0:14:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Those sparkles...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.73,0:14:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,They're my tears.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.47,0:14:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But from those circumstances...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.57,0:14:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,...new warriors who surpassed\Neven my ideals were born.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.48,0:14:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm referring to the\NGundam pilots.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.18,0:14:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Father?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.18,0:14:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,FATHER!!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.85,0:14:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You're afraid of dying,\Naren't you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.16,0:14:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you shouldn't be\Nfighting in the first place!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.43,0:14:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Tradition appears blurred\Nalongside their pure feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.63,0:14:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,From a historical point...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.57,0:14:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,...warriors who lost what\Nthey were protecting...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.34,0:14:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,...and who were betrayed,\Nare losers.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.91,0:14:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But they don't recognize that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.08,0:14:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only that...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.41,0:14:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,...but they retain a strong will\Nto continue fighting.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.68,0:14:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm doing everything I can...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.55,0:15:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,...in case "something drastic"\Ndoes happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.27,0:15:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,If everything has gone mad...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.73,0:15:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,...then I'll just fight,\Nbelieving in myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.77,0:15:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The emotions of those\Nconsidered beautiful...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.01,0:15:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,...are always full of sorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.44,0:15:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And honored tradition disappears\Nin the cry of the weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.14,0:15:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Winners of a war will eventually\Ndecline in history to be losers...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.45,0:15:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,...only then can they cultivate\Na new energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.82,0:15:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Treize, what are you getting at?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.52,0:15:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to be a loser.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.99,0:15:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You're saying that you want\NRomefeller headquarters...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.00,0:15:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,...to take OZ out of\Nyour control?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.07,0:15:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't wish to see any blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.18,0:15:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, we must take your\Nservices into account.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.58,0:15:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I hereby confine you to\NRomefeller headquarters!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.89,0:16:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,With a fancy gun that has\Nforgotten the meaning of war...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.79,0:16:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,...I'd feel no emotion...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.79,0:16:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,...even if I were to shoot an\Nenemy through the heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.43,0:16:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not that a pure person\Nhas no direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.86,0:16:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It's that their mind is free.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.57,0:16:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The Lunar Base is entering\Nthe firing range...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.24,0:16:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,...of Barge's beam cannon.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.08,0:16:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,A troop of Taurus mobile dolls\Ndispatched by the Lunar Base...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.21,0:16:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,...is approaching.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.41,0:16:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,They're ready to attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.01,0:16:34.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Communication with the\NLunar Base restored!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.48,0:16:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Lady Une.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.05,0:16:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Transporting the Barge wasn't{\i0}\N{\i1}in today's plans, was it.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.16,0:16:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The mobile dolls were all{\i0}\N{\i1}prepared to attack you.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.19,0:16:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,A merciless weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.13,0:16:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that what the mobile doll is?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.03,0:16:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Precisely.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.47,0:16:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We've completed our mass{\i0}\N{\i1}production system here.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.20,0:16:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We've produced superb soldiers...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.27,0:16:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}...that will allow Romefeller{\i0}\N{\i1}to exercise order on Earth.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.51,0:17:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I understand why Treize\Ndislikes the mobile dolls.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.25,0:17:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Pardon?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.21,0:17:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Treize fell in love with people.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.52,0:17:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And with the death of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.05,0:17:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Something about death intensely\Nappeals to people's emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.46,0:17:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The emotions that the dead give,\Ndenying or affirming battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.33,0:17:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,High emotions lead to\Nextreme choices.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.96,0:17:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The act of receiving death\Nis a true soldier's demeanor.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.27,0:17:34.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Isn't that how the weak{\i0}\N{\i1}would think?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.78,0:17:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We created these immortal{\i0}\N{\i1}mobile dolls...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.18,0:17:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}...and will build a future{\i0}\N{\i1}of battle that disregards death...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.45,0:17:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}...and in which death isn't{\i0}\N{\i1}a factor.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.05,0:17:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Tubarov.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.19,0:17:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you realize?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.76,0:17:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not that mobile dolls\Ntranscend death.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.56,0:17:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,They're merely replacing those\Nwho are afraid to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.16,0:17:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,One cannot go into a war\Nexpecting to be defeated.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.23,0:18:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It doesn't matter whether{\i0}\N{\i1}you win or lose.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.70,0:18:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Emotions are honed by{\i0}\N{\i1}continuing to fight.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.94,0:18:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And a day comes when{\i0}\N{\i1}lost souls are rewarded.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.35,0:18:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I fail to understand\Nwhat you're getting at.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.45,0:18:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That's exactly why you\Nand I are enemies!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.76,0:18:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Order the mobile dolls to\Nattack Fortress Barge.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.60,0:18:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll have the beam cannon\Ntargeting this base!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.00,0:18:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,They won't realize Barge\Nis a decoy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.44,0:18:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't predict the damage\NBarge's beam cannon...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.67,0:18:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,...would cause the Lunar Base.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.51,0:18:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Make it through this, Barge.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.25,0:18:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It won't be long.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.82,0:18:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten Leos have crossed\Nour defense line!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.15,0:18:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,They're attacking the gates\Nwhere most of the guards...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.16,0:18:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,...have gone to stop Barge!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.72,0:18:58.99,Default,,0,0,0,,They know where all our\Nmobile dolls are situated.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.06,0:19:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,That makes it interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.87,0:19:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Take over the production{\i0}\N{\i1}factory of the mobile dolls!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.50,0:19:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are you going, Colonel?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.71,0:19:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm releasing the Gundam pilots!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.61,0:19:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Treize and I both want that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.59,0:19:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The enemy isn't pursuing.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.16,0:19:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we'll defend this position.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.82,0:19:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Captain!!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.16,0:19:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.19,0:19:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The new mobile suits are\Nalready operating!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.04,0:19:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope I'm not too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.01,0:19:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you're not, we'll\Nexecute them anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.05,0:19:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I ask that you\Nexecute me too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.92,0:19:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,In the past, failure meant\Ncertain death at OZ.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.83,0:20:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Shoot me, Tubarov.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.86,0:20:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,To confirm your beliefs.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.87,0:20:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Lady Une.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.53,0:20:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You were far too lenient.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.60,0:20:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,As a soldier, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.44,0:20:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But as a civilian\NI lived a strict life.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.07,0:20:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's only 70% complete.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.97,0:20:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We can't put up much{\i0}\N{\i1}of a fight!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.04,0:20:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's amazing that{\i0}\N{\i1}we're even alive.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.87,0:20:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Can't complain.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.08,0:20:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Wanna escape?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.24,0:20:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,After we pay them back.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.46,0:21:47.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The charm of you pilots\Nthrew everything out of order.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.60,0:21:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Your pure hearts are suffering...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.26,0:21:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,...in a world where answers\Ncannot be found.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.83,0:21:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Those that think tenderly\Nabout you in that situation...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.17,0:21:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,...realize just how powerless\Nthey themselves are.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.81,0:22:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,They become hasty,\Nand are crushed.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.58,0:22:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But please continue shining,\Nbrave warriors.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.55,0:22:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And let me continue loving you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.55,0:23:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Hearing of Treize's confinement...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.52,0:23:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,...OZ soldiers called\Nthe "Treize Faction"...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.92,0:23:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,...enter a battle with\NRomefeller.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.83,0:23:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The Virgo mobile dolls\Nsent to Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.03,0:23:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,...have tremendous assault\Ncapabilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.40,0:23:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The Foundation wants to destroy\Nthe Gundams and their allies...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.44,0:23:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,...seeing them as a symbol\Nof opposition.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.24,0:23:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,They order the Gundam pilots'\Nexecution.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.77,0:23:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, on Gundam Wing, Episode 26,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.76,0:23:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,"The Eternal Flame of the Shooting Stars".
